                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-20T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 20, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 20—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>267. Embassy’s July 20, 3 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>According to Japanese and Chinese military sources, firing broke out at
                        about 3 this afternoon in the vicinity of Marco Polo Bridge between Japanese
                        and Chinese forces.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Major General Kawabe, who is understood to be in command Japanese forces
                        in that area, is reliably reported to have informed a foreigner about half
                        an hour before the outbreak that in his opinion the 37th Division needs a
                        very strict and severe lesson.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
